See docs/proposals/044-unified-name-resolution.md. Unify the divergent rustland/scaland resolution algorithms into one, replace export-whitelisting with import-side disambiguation of inherited operations (decide option B1/B2/B3/B4 — recommended B2: inheritance aliases not copies), make visibility 'visible-by-default + internal hides', then strip export statements from stdlib and document the algorithm in kernel-language.md.

GATING DECISION: pick disambiguation rule B in the proposal before implementing. Validated already: scaland Model C is clean (167 green); rustland breaks 87 wi_tests on the Eq/Ordered 'eq' ambiguity because export currently disambiguates inherited ops.",
