fact WorkItem(
  id: "WI-399",
  description: "Typer: lift projection elimination from check_apply_iter ALONE to the unify_types projection arms (the design intended ALTITUDE -- typing.rs around 7400+ sort_ref/projection arms hold the and-mut subst to mint fresh vars + add constraints). Today eliminate_type_projections runs only in check_apply_iter (operation-call return/effect positions, typing.rs:2999-3008); a projection at a LET binding, a RULE body, or a HIGHER-ORDER application site is not eliminated. The original WI-376 description specified elimination at the sort_ref/projection arms of unify_types ~7400+ as the pure-classifier-cannot-mint placement; the concrete delivery took the check_apply_iter shortcut. Generalize so any unify-boundary encounter with an ExprCarried head eliminates it (synthesis-time constraint discharge where the receiver type is known; loud error where it is not). Design: expansion-during-unification.md sec.4 (Placement) + sec.7 Layer 2. Spun out of WI-376. Rust-only.",
  acceptance: [ToolPasses("cargo-test")],
