fact Tag(name: "typing", workitem: "WI-399")
fact Feedback(content: "SPLIT 2026-06-05 (user-authorized: \"keep 376; spin out 4 seams\"). The 4 mechanical/architectural follow-on seams from the PROGRESS note are now their own typing tickets: WI-396 (effects s.E -- effect-position projection), WI-397 (compound receiver a.b.T -- Node carrier), WI-398 (cross-param projection + load-time strictness/cycle graph), WI-399 (altitude -- eliminate at the unify_types projection arms, not only check_apply_iter). Each depends on WI-379 and builds on the delivered ExprCarried substrate; deliverable independently of the abstract decision below.\n\nWI-376 RETAINS ITS OWN ACCEPTANCE = the abstract-receiver stays-poly half (remaining items 1 + 5): the concrete/abstract receiver split via ONE signature, where an ABSTRACT receiver c:C projecting c.T resolves against C declared-interface member as a rigid receiver-tied type that STAYS POLYMORPHIC to the concrete call (today it errors soundly instead) -- plus the cross-sort provider DIVERGENT member name (project off declared param sort + provider, not the arg raw sort). This is a SEMANTIC-MODEL change (WI-393 carrier/provider machinery) and is PARKED pending a USER DESIGN DECISION.\n\nWI-376 now depends_on WI-398 + WI-399 so the abstract-stays-poly model is decided/implemented against the COMPLETE projection substrate (synthesis-order strictness + full-altitude unify-boundary elimination). It stays Claimed but BLOCKED until those land; the loop should deliver WI-396..399 first, then resume WI-376 and surface the semantic-model design question to the user (do NOT auto-guess the abstract model).", at: "2026-06-05T16:49:38Z", workitem: "WI-376", author: "claude")
fact Feedback(content: "DELIVERED 2026-06-05 (commit ec10d77, full anthill-core green 1207). SMALLER than the ticket anticipated: the classifier (type_expr_to_value -> type_expr_to_child -> try_expr_carried_projection) + eliminator (op_has_projection already includes effects; the check_apply_iter effect loop already calls eliminate_type_projections per effect; project_type_member reads the E member generically) were ALL already wired by the WI-376 concrete delivery. The ONLY blocker was infer_effects_row_requires (load.rs) strict-resolving every Simple effect name via remap_name, which JOINED the dotted s.E -> spurious UnresolvedName before the projection could be classified. FIX = skip multi-segment effect names there (a row variable is always a single-segment sort E = ? name). Independent adversarial review confirmed: no auto-require dropped (multi-segment is never a free row variable; SortAlias is keyed by sort symbol not param), and a malformed multi-segment effect name STILL errors loudly via the parallel type_expr_to_value path (loud-error principle upheld). project_type_member projects E off the receiver type; l.E on List (no effect member) is a loud missing-member error per design sec.5 (the written row is the route to carry E, not a projection) -- never a silent pure default. Works bare (effects s.E) AND inside a written row (effects {s.E}). 4 tests in wi376_projection_test.rs (threads {Branch} concrete; pure caller rejected; l.E loud; {s.E} row). Stale typing.rs:2996 follow-on comment updated.", at: "2026-06-05T17:19:47Z", workitem: "WI-396", author: "claude")
fact Feedback(content: "DESIGN DRAFTED 2026-06-05 (docs/design/path-dependent-types.md). The parked abstract-receiver stays-poly keystone crystallized, via WI-397 design dialogue (the DataProvider use-case), into a full PATH-DEPENDENT TYPES model. Key decisions captured: (1) identity is SEMANTIC over the receiver VALUE = unification of the receiver expression up to the substitution (let y=z => y.T==z.T), NOT nominal-over-the-syntactic-path (the divergence from Scala AND ML translucent sums); (2) the two rules of the spine -- GROUNDING = track the expression type through control flow (flow-typing; Scala tracked is the static analogue), IDENTITY = unify expression types; (3) equality is the dependent-type-theory DEFINITIONAL CONVERSION restricted to three reductions -- zeta (receiver-unify) + delta (manifest member grounds) + eta (s.Sort reifies the whole type) -- over a NON-INJECTIVE ExprCarried head (never decompose p.M=?=q.M into p=?=q; rides WI-370 custom-unification-at-head); (4) inference = collect constraints, defer maximally, solve at end, DELAY-never-reject, with the soundness invariant = loud-error-over-silent-skip lifted to constraints (every deferred constraint confirmed/refuted/surfaced, never silently dropped) + 011 three-level residual accounting (ill / well-with-obligations / universally-typed). One fully-worked PARAMETRIC example (State[P] holding a provider) needs NO new term representation -- the occurrence type-slot carries it; PLAIN-field (refinement, Scala tracked-style) and (expr).M (grammar + stability) are deferred. The model SUBSUMES the seams as facets: WI-397 (compound receiver) + WI-398 (cross-param + synthesis order) + WI-399 (eliminate at unify boundary) + WI-384 (constructor infers P) + WI-370 (non-injective head). NOT YET RATIFIED -- this is the session design draft; the abstract half stays parked until the user confirms the model and the build order off it.", at: "2026-06-05T21:29:45Z", workitem: "WI-376", author: "claude")
fact Feedback(content: "DESIGN ADOPTED 2026-06-05 (user: \"WI-376 can use this design\"). docs/design/path-dependent-types.md IS now WI-376 design: the abstract-receiver stays-poly half = path-dependent types per the doc (value-unification identity; grounding by control-flow type-tracking; zeta/delta/eta conversion over a NON-INJECTIVE ExprCarried head; abstraction = a static CALL-SITE CONTRACT via requires/ensures; base model forbids the abstracting return so it is escape-free). No longer \"not yet ratified\" -- design decided. Implementation needs beyond the existing seams (WI-384/397/398/399, +WI-370 as a dependency) are being mapped; new WIs to be filed for the gaps (equality non-injective head+delay; no-sealing/interface-expressible-return check; ensures-manifest translucent returns [deferred]; realization to host [deferred]).", at: "2026-06-05T22:10:41Z", workitem: "WI-376", author: "claude")
fact WorkItem(
  id: "WI-400",
  description: "Typer: ExprCarried is a NON-INJECTIVE custom-unification head -- the equality-soundness core of path-dependent identity (docs/design/path-dependent-types.md sec.3-4). Unifying two path types p.M =?= q.M: delta-GROUND both sides first (project the manifest member off the receiver type) then unify the results; if both stay NEUTRAL (rigid, no manifest), CHECK SIGMA-EQUALITY of the receivers -- resolve each through the current substitution (follow the let/unification aliases it records) and compare structurally; a non-binding CHECK (are they ALREADY equal under the substitution), NOT unification (could they be MADE equal -- that would be the unsound non-injective decomposition). let y=z makes y,z sigma-equal so y.T==z.T; two distinct receivers stay distinct, never forced equal (projection is not injective: peek(a).T and peek(b).T can both be Int without a=b). A flexible-receiver goal (a receiver that is a logic variable -- arises only in RULE BODIES, never op signatures) SUSPENDS and wakes when its receivers bind (the resolver delay/rotation), under the no-silent-drop discipline (every deferred constraint ends confirmed/refuted/surfaced, never silently accepted; set-level final solve). CONSUMER of the WI-370 custom-unification-at-discrim-node feature (NOT WI-370 itself, whose driver is op-bodies). Underpins WI-376 abstract-stays-poly. Rust-only (typer).",
  acceptance: [ToolPasses("cargo-test")],
  depends_on: ["WI-399"],
  status: Delivered(agent: "claude", at: "2026-06-09T10:33:22Z"))

fact Tag(name: "typing", workitem: "WI-400")
fact WorkItem(
  id: "WI-401",
  description: "Typer/loader: reject the ABSTRACTING RETURN so the base model is escape-free (no sealing) -- the well-formedness gate of docs/design/path-dependent-types.md sec.5. A return type must be INTERFACE-EXPRESSIBLE: concrete, or rooted at the operation OWN inputs (params/type-params), or (deferred admit-form) made so by an ensures manifest. Forbid a return annotation more abstract than the value the body returns (seal(s: SubscriberStore) -> DataProvider = s): that opaque, local-rooted abstract member is the ONLY thing that escapes (ML avoidance problem). Implements the strict-first build note. Per design a rigid path roots at {top-level/global, op-interface, hidden-local}; this check removes the hidden-local introducer (sealing), so every rigid path roots at an in-scope param/global. Gated at the unify-boundary elaboration where returns are checked. Rust-only (typer/loader).",
  acceptance: [ToolPasses("cargo-test")],
  depends_on: ["WI-399"],
  status: Delivered(agent: "claude", at: "2026-06-09T15:47:00Z"))

