fact Feedback(workitem: "WI-470", author: "user", content: "OUTCOME/SCOPE (delivered as arrow/effect-row occurrence-primary): ec8c619 flips make_arrow_value to always-Node (ground children ride TypeChild::Ground; a row-tail folds as open(tail) not present(var)) + a Rc::ptr_eq unify fast-path + carrier-agnostic resolved_type_is_ground/node_type_is_ground/denoted_value_is_closed (value-in-type three-way: closed->conformance-checked, free var->inference, binder-relative value-place->alignment-aware validate_callback_effect_row). d42682c makes bind_spec_params_from_carrier read receiver bindings carrier-agnostically (preserves a poisoned-Node parameterized receiver's bindings). DESCOPED: parameterized/named-tuple/nominal types INTENTIONALLY stay hash-consed -- a TermId carries the binding fully (no erasure) and IS the load-bearing index key (by_sort/fact_dedup), the representation-note 'nominal, heavily-shared' category; flipping closed parameterizeds to Node added binding-erasure risk at every .as_term() consumer for NO payoff (048's guard needs effect-rows/arrows, not List[T]). The full 'occurrences primary, no silent Value->TermId downgrade' realization is the as_term sweep, filed as WI-477.", at: "2026-06-15T13:15:27Z")
fact WorkItem(id: "WI-470", description: some(value: "Migrate Type/EffectExpression from hash-consed Term to an occurrence (node-world) carrier; keep hash-consing as an OPTIONAL derived Node->TermId index only where dedup/equality pays (row canonicalization, the unify_effect_rows shared-field fast-path, recoverable via Rc::ptr_eq). Rationale: the representation note says hash-consing is not required for type-hood and is disclaimed for binders/arrows; this continues the WI-246/251 node migration (rule bodies and op bodies are already NodeOccurrence). Scope is the whole Type spine, NOT just the row: a hash-consed arrow term cannot hold an occurrence child (WI-251), so the inner EffectExpression cannot migrate without the enclosing arrow/Type. Much is already carrier-agnostic: unify_effect_rows is generic over TermView, subst.bind_value binds Value::Node (WI-375 E={Modify[c]}, WI-342 type params), substitute_ref_syms_occ rewrites occurrences, Positioned/make_positioned bridges binder leaves into terms, discrim keys on structural DiscrimKey; WI-375 already node-carries WRITTEN effect rows. Remaining holdouts: term-building construction (make_effect_expression_*/build_canonical_effects_rows/make_effects_rows_type), making decompose_effect_row structurally walk a Node-carried row, the arrow/Type cascade per WI-251, reification (extract->TypeExtractor) and any TermId-keyed row indices. Payoff: proposal 048's guarded-effect guard becomes List[NodeOccurrence] uniform with rule/op bodies, dissolving the term-vs-occurrence split documented in proposal 048 open question F."), context: none, acceptance: [ToolPasses(tool: "cargo-test", params: none)], depends_on: some(value: ["WI-471"]), generates: none, requires_capability: none, status: Delivered(agent: "claude", at: "2026-06-15T13:18:11Z"))
